    "abstractNote": "Modern Aramaeans hesitate to use and teach their spoken language, the Aramaic of the Tur Abdin, as a written language. The author discusses possible reasons and argues that the discourse in the community on the history of the language causes this rejection. Therefore, this discourse requires a paradigm shift to change the awareness of the speakers of their language. Only then, the textualization will receive recognition.",
